65
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:12,760
Yeah.

66
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:14,280
Roger that, Captain.

67
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,600
With the way they're
working together,

68
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,640
the 17th should win this match.

69
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:18,880
KALIAN (ON PHONE): Maybe, but‐‐

70
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,240
But what?

71
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:22,800
There are wild
cards in this game.

72
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:27,320
And not just for the 17th,
but also for the 5th.

73
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,400
The man that many call
Zuellni's greatest warrior

74
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,360
has just appeared.

75
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,680
The captain of the 5th
Platoon, Gorneo Lueckens.

76
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:41,120
A Lueckens?

77
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:41,920
But how?

78
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,840
Oh, that's right.

79
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:45,280
Gorneo hails from Glendan,
the same city as Layfon,

80
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,120
doesn't he?

81
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,320
KALIAN (ON PHONE):
Yes What's more,

82
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,200
he's the younger brother
of Savaris Lueckens,

83
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,480
a keeper of the Heaven's Blade.

84
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,280
You could almost
say it's fate.

85
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:55,280
Not likely.

86
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,800
No matter how far you run,
the past will always catch

87
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:01,040
up with you, won't it, Layfon?

88
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:03,400
Tempered Transformation
Hardened Steel Strike!

89
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,800
I'm not done with you yet.

90
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,720
In fact, I'm just
getting started!

91
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:35,880
He repelled my entire attack.

92
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:39,120
SHANTE: Leave him to me.

93
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:39,920
Shante.

94
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,200
What are you doing out here?

95
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,560
Fire Kei Great
Projectile Flash!

96
00:05:58,640 --> 00:05:59,440
Dammit.

97
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:01,320
I really thought that move
would have taken him out.

98
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,320
Why aren't you guarding
the flag right now?

99
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,040
Because if we take
him out right away,

100
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:06,840
his platoon won't have
a chance of winning.

101
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:07,720
Don't be stupid.

102
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,560
They can still win
this without him.

103
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,520
SHANTE: Look!

104
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:12,040
[HISSING]

105
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,440
[SHOUT]

106
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,400
Uh?

107
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:22,640
What is he doing?

108
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,320
The thousand man attack.

109
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:27,280
KALIAN: To think, he's even
mastered this technique.

110
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:28,080
Shante.

111
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:28,840
Find him.

112
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,120
There he is.

113
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:40,080
You're mine, pal!

114
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:41,080
[GUNSHOT]

115
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:48,600
ANNOUNCER (OVER SPEAKER):
And that's it, folks.

116
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:52,640
Today's win is another
victory for the 17th Platoon.

117
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:55,360
That was excellent
Tempered Kei.

118
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,200
Hey, listen.

119
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:59,160
I never thought I'd run into a
Lueckens here, of all places.

120
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:01,000
Do you think complimenting
my Kei technique

121
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,240
will get you a
hand shake from me?

122
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,040
No, I don't.

123
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,600
Hey, you!

124
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,400
This isn't over!

125
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,440
You're going down, you hear me?

126
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,680
If it's the last thing I‐‐
GORNEO: Shante.

127
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,720
SHANTE: God dammit, Gorneo!

128
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,040
Let me go!

129
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,520
That guy's toast!

130
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:21,200
You better watch your
back, buddy, because I'm

131
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,440
gonna be coming for you!

132
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:23,720
All right.
We did it.

133
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,720
Let's celebrate.

134
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,320
MIFI: Thanks, everybody.

135
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:36,200
Now, in honor of the 17th
Platoon's second straight win,

136
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:38,640
I'm singing one more
song for those guys!

137
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:41,640
[CHEERING]

138
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:46,600
(SINGING) Won't you tell
me what you're thinking?

139
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,520
You know, you should
sing next, handsome.

140
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:51,440
If you don't, that little girl's
never gonna let go of that mic.

141
00:07:51,440 --> 00:07:52,920
I don't think so.

142
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:56,720
I do sing, but I never do it
for crowds in places like this.

143
00:07:56,720 --> 00:08:00,760
When exactly do you
sing, then, gorgeous?

144
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:03,840
SHARNID: Only when I'm alone
and with a special someone.

145
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,640
BARTENDER: Mhm.

146
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,240
And is there a
special someone here

147
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,920
you want to sing to tonight?

148
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,400
Uh, this is awkward.

149
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,200
Hey Sharnid.

150
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,360
You did really great today.

151
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,160
Thanks, Nina.

152
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,640
It's been quite a
while since you've gotten

153
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:14,600
to fight in the front lines.

154
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,680
So how was it?

155
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,600
Not bad.

156
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,280
I loved the looks
on the 5th's faces

157
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,480
when they saw I could
use Jusho Jutsu.

158
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:22,480
It took time to learn,
but their expressions

159
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,680
made it all worth it.

160
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,920
Yeah, I'm sure it did.

161
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,800
Your mastering close
range combat skills is a

162
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,680
serious benefit to the platoon.

163
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,440
These new techniques you
and Layfon have learned

164
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,040
will increase our strategies.

165
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:34,320
Won't be long before we're
totally undefeatable.

166
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,120
Come on, Nina.

167
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:35,880
Admit it.

168
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:36,680
I'm the bomb, aren't I?

169
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:37,520
Yeah, all right.

170
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:38,480
I suppose so.

171
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:41,160
But just this one time, I'm
admit it, you're the bomb.

172
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:42,560
Think you better
watch it or that's

173
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:43,640
gonna go straight to his head.

174
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,440
I know.

175
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,200
That's why he's never
gonna hear it again.

176
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,240
That's mean.

177
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,160
NINA: Sorry.

178
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,200
HARLEY: You'll like this, Nina.

179
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,000
It's good.

180
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,160
NINA: Thanks a lot, Harley.

181
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,440
SHARNID: Hey, I'll
take some too, dude.

182
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,360
HARLEY: The bomb can
go get his own things.

183
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,160
SHARNID: The hell?

184
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,720
Hurry up and do it, Mayshie.

185
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,520
No.

186
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,840
I don't think now's
the right time.

187
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,040
What are you saying?

188
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,880
If you're not gonna give it
to him now, when will you?

189
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,000
Layfon just left.

190
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,840
What's the deal with
that guy tonight anyway?

191
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,760
FELLI (VOICEOVER): I
want to feel the world.

192
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,840
This world.

193
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,560
And beyond the vast darkness.

194
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,440
SHANTE: I just don't get it.

195
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:33,400
He's your enemy, right?

196
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,240
GORNEO: Of course he
is, but I mean, come on.

197
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:37,200
We couldn't just throw
away a competition.

198
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,480
SHANTE: But it was the
perfect opportunity.

199
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,480
You don't know when you'll
get one like that again.

200
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,520
GORNEO: It's OK.

201
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,320
And trust me.

202
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:46,480
No matter how much time passes,
my anger won't fade a bit.

203
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,480
Really

204
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:49,600
Mark my words, Layfon Alseif.

205
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,320
I'm gonna make you pay for
your crime one way or another.

206
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:57,240
It's her.

207
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,720
Why are you here?

208
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:01,720
I'm not obligated to answer
that for either of you.

209
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,560
Oh yeah?

210
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,840
That's the 17th for you.

211
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:06,360
The same guys who let a
coward into their ranks.

212
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,360
I guess you're a coward too!

213
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,160
What do you mean?

214
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:10,080
What the?

215
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,480
You don't even know?

216
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,280
GORNEO: Shante.

217
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,120
Hmph.

218
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:22,800
What did she mean?

219
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:38,200
[GUNFIRE]

220
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:49,640
So Biggie's in
one of those, huh?

221
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,160
Looks like time's running out.

222
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,640
LAYFON: Nina?

223
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:58,480
NINA: What's up?

224
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,680
LAYFON: Don't you come in later?

225
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:00,840
NINA: I thought I'd
come in a little

226
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:02,360
early so I could see
Zuellni for a bit,

227
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,560
but she won't show herself.

228
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:04,360
Oh.

229
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,600
OK.
‐ Hey.

230
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:06,720
When we're finished,
do you think

231
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:07,760
you could spare a few minutes?

232
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,560
Huh?

233
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:10,160
I came up with
this great strategy

234
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,440
for the next competition.

235
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:15,120
I'd like to hear what you think.

236
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,240
What is it?

237
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:18,520
Well, to be honest, it's you.

238
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:19,400
Uh.

239
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,240
You enjoy fighting, don't you?

240
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,600
You even look forward to it.

241
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,400
No.

242
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:26,240
That isn't true at all.

243
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,040
OK.

244
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,320
Who am I trying to fool?

245
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,120
Of course it is.

246
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:31,240
And I enjoy every
bit of it, Layfon.

247
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,920
I'm really happy now.

248
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:34,320
We're winning, and
that's something I've

249
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,800
dreamed about for a long time.

250
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,800
There was a municipal challenge.

251
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,880
It was two years ago.

252
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:45,280
At stake was ownership
of a surname line,

253
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:48,240
which is critical for the
survival of every Regios.

254
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:51,520
It was a grueling and
dangerous challenge.

255
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,120
We came so close.

256
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,760
Victory was almost ours.

257
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:57,800
But in the end, we lost.

258
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,760
And the other
platoon, I remember

259
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,760
they were so happy, cheering
and hugging one another.

260
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:05,760
That's when I thought,
that's what I want.

261
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:08,200
To stand with my team
after we've successfully

262
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,600
protected our city.

263
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:12,920
To be victorious and share
our happiness together.

264
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:18,000
Bit by bit, my dream's
finally coming true at last.

265
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,400
I feel it.

266
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:22,760
If we can keep
fighting, we'll win.

267
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:23,640
Fighting?

268
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,680
That's why you're happy?

269
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:25,480
NINA: Yeah.

270
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,200
That's where you and I differ.

271
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:32,120
I've never been
happy about fighting.

272
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,800
Not once.

273
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,320
It doesn't matter
what kind of victory

274
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:38,160
you achieve either, because
in the world we live in,

275
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:40,640
winning has no real
meaning at all.

276
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:42,200
What are you talking about?

277
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,720
MAN: Oh, there you are.

278
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:46,000
The student council
president's calling you.

279
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,920
I wonder what he wants.

280
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:49,880
[KNOCKING]

281
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:51,640
NINA: We're here, sir.

282
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:57,800
Argh.

283
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:59,120
KALIAN: Thank you
all for coming.

284
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:01,560
Do you have any idea as
to why I've summoned you.

285
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:02,800
Not again.

286
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,240
The Contaminoids?

287
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:06,160
Not for us, thankfully.

288
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,560
But they may be involved
in this matter, though.

289
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:10,800
What happened?

290
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:11,600
Hm?

291
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,280
LEERIN (VOICEOVER): Wait.

292
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,440
I'm being targeted?

293
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,440
Me?

294
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:29,840
SAVARIS (VOICEOVER):
It appears so.

295
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:32,160
Sorry, but just to be
safe, Lintens and I will

296
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,480
be watching over you covertly.

297
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,760
LEERIN (VOICEOVER):
I don't understand.

298
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:37,680
Who's after me and why?

299
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:39,720
LINTENS (VOICEOVER): I
believe we said no questions.

300
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:46,000
Guess I'm just
imagining things.

301
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,480
SYNORA: No doubt about
it, these are the best.

302
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,760
These.

303
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:52,640
So perfect, so
round, so squeezable.

304
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:54,560
You've got the best
ones I've ever seen.

305
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:55,440
Oh, Synora.

306
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:57,160
It's you.

307
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:59,400
In fact, I'd rate your
chest a million points.

308
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,400
LEERIN: Synora!

309
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,400
You shouldn't assign
points to a person's chest.

310
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,880
SYNORA: Or jump around on
a steep flight of stairs.

311
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,400
Hm.

312
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,680
You don't say.

313
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:13,040
LEERIN: It is reassuring to
know that I've got two Heaven's

314
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:16,200
Blades watching over
me, but even so,

315
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,160
I'm really worried about this.

316
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:19,160
Well, you shouldn't be.

317
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:21,360
They said they were doing it
just to be safe, didn't they?

318
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,320
They did.

319
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,120
But still.

320
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:28,040
The only thing we
can tell you right now

321
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,840
is this has something to
do with Layfon Alseif.

322
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:38,160
Hm?

323
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:39,080
It's getting dark.

324
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,120
I better get home now.

325
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:42,120
SYNORA: Promise me you'll
be careful, all right?

326
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:43,240
I will.

327
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,040
Bye.

328
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:49,080
Savaris.

329
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:49,880
Yes, your majesty.

330
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:51,000
What can I do for you?

331
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,680
Now, didn't I tell you
that you were forbidden

332
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:53,680
from calling me that here?

333
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:54,480
Right.

334
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,320
You certainly did.

335
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:57,640
I'm sorry about
that, Queen Alsheyra.

336
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:59,560
Uh, that's something else
I'm not supposed to call you,

337
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:00,360
isn't it?

338
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:02,400
I do apologize, Synora.

339
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,200
Jeez.

340
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,920
You're such an idiot.

341
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:07,040
MAN (ON INTERCOM): They
eighth gate is now on standby.

342
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:10,040
Please complete Land
Roller inspections ASAP.

343
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,200
The current temperature is 13‐‐

344
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,200
SHARNID: It was attacked
by Contaminoids?

345
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,000
NINA: We don't know.

346
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,120
All we do know is that
it's along our current path

347
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,120
and has stopped moving.

348
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,600
Unless something
changes, Zuellni

349
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,160
will reach it in three days.

350
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,720
[YAWN]
OK.

351
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:23,680
So you go and check it
out and see if it's safe,

352
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:25,200
and then come back, all right?

353
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:27,520
Good luck with that one, Nina.

354
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:29,760
You're coming too, so wake
up and start getting changed,

355
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:30,680
you slacker.

356
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,680
Yes, ma'am.

357
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,080
HARLEY: If we weren't
in such a rush,

358
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,640
I might have had
your new Adamandite

359
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,360
ready for you to take along.

360
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,280
LAYFON: A new one?

361
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:38,120
HARLEY: Yeah.

362
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:41,240
It's more of an anti‐personnel
weapon, and lighter too.

363
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:44,440
But because of that, you can't
trade out different DITEs.

364
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:46,880
I need a little more time with
it and it should be ready.

365
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:48,720
Well, better get back to it.

366
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,560
FELLI: Fon‐Fon.

367
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:52,240
Huh?

368
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:53,720
Yes, Senior Felli?

369
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,840
Ah!

370
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:55,680
Sorry.

371
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:58,040
I don't understand why we're
going out with the 5th Platoon.

372
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:58,800
Oh.

373
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,760
Well, according to the
student council president,

374
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:03,480
none of the other platoons
have enough atmosphere suits.

375
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:05,000
That's what he told you?

376
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,480
I think he's full of it.

377
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,280
Huh?

378
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:12,200
Hmph.

379
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:23,000
Monkey.

380
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,480
Well, I'm ready
to move out when

381
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,920
you are, oh fearless leader.

382
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:26,720
Oh, hey.

383
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,520
Sharnid.

384
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,720
Sorry, but could
you do me a favor

385
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,480
and ride with Felli instead?

386
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,640
SHARNID: Uh, sure, I guess.

387
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:38,840
SHANTE: Here's an idea.

388
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:39,920
GORNEO: What's that?

389
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,000
SHANTE: We could settle it now.

390
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,240
Make it look like an accident.

391
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:44,560
GORNEO: It's not that easy.

392
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:46,760
You saw how powerful
he was, didn't you?

393
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:47,600
SHANTE: Yeah, but still.

394
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:50,160
Couldn't we try to
take him by surprise?

395
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:51,920
GORNEO: If you think he
could be defeated like that,

396
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,640
you've got another thing coming.

397
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:56,840
Remember, he's not some pushover
but a former Heaven's Blade.

398
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,800
SHANTE: Yeah, well, so what?

399
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,120
Who cares?

400
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,040
I still think you're a
lot stronger than he is.

401
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:13,400
NINA: And I thought
I finally understood

402
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,400
things a little better.

403
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,240
LAYFON: What?

404
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:16,640
NINA: But I don't
get you at all.

405
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,480
LAYFON: That came
out of nowhere.

406
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,920
NINA: So did winning
has no real meaning.

407
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:23,040
I still can't get over
you telling me that.

408
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:25,160
LAYFON: I wouldn't give
it too much thought.

409
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,680
I just said what I was thinking.

410
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:27,720
That's all.

411
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:30,320
NINA: But you still
meant it, right?

412
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:32,040
Winning a competition
means gaining

413
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:33,840
strength and confidence.

414
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:36,520
Winning a municipal battle
means gaining a cernium mine.

415
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:39,000
Something we need to survive.

416
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,440
Do those things have
no meaning either?

417
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,480
LAYFON: Look.
There it is.

418
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:42,640
Coming up to the west.

419
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,640
NINA: Are you gonna answer me?

420
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:44,720
LAYFON: Let's
discuss this later.

421
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:00,600
SHARNID: The outer
gate's busted.

422
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,720
Looks like we're gonna
have to enter from the top.

423
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:05,120
NINA: Before we do that,
Felli, can you tell

424
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,560
us how things are in there?

425
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,600
FELLI: I'm only
getting fragments,

426
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,760
but I don't sense anything
dangerous right now.

427
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,760
MAN (ON RADIO): Captain Antalk.

428
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:13,760
This is the 5th platoon.

429
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,160
We've finished our recon
around the east gate.

430
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,120
NINA: How's it look?

431
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:19,040
MAN (ON RADIO): The dock
is completely destroyed.

432
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,680
Captain Lueckens and
some of the others

433
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:23,480
are now trying to enter through
a damaged external section.

434
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,320
NINA: Layfon.

435
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:25,320
Can you get in?

436
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,120
LAYFON: Yeah.

437
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:27,240
Restoration 02.

438
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:32,880
FELLI: Will you take me as well?

439
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:35,680
LAYFON: Sure thing.

440
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:36,480
Hold on tight.

441
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:40,920
NINA: Get ready.

442
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,160
We're going up next.

443
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:45,000
SHARNID: Roger, boss.

444
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,920
FELLI: You don't
have to do that.

445
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:50,000
I can guarantee this
place is safe, Fon‐Fon.

446
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,720
LAYFON: It's kind
of a habit of mine.

447
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:54,520
I always like to make
sure for myself, you know?

448
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,320
FELLI: But it's unnecessary.

449
00:18:56,320 --> 00:18:59,440
If you're going to waste
energy like that, at least

450
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:02,520
try to be more polite about it.

451
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:03,560
LAYFON: Sorry, Felli.

452
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:05,040
NINA: Well?

453
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:06,440
LAYFON: No bioactivity.

454
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:08,000
NINA: Air filters?

455
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:11,240
FELLI: They're working fine.

456
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:12,080
As you can see.

457
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:23,720
SHARNID: Whoa.

458
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:24,520
Creepy.

459
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:25,840
This place is a real ghost town.

460
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:31,680
LAYFON: I think it's
safe to say this place

461
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,120
was attacked by Contaminoids.

462
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:35,680
NINA: Yeah.

463
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:37,320
We should look for survivors.

464
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:38,840
LAYFON: Right.

465
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:41,640
SHARNID: I don't know if we
should get our hopes up, guys.

466
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:44,240
FELLI: If they sought shelter,
what about that plaza up ahead?

467
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:45,040
NINA: Yeah.

468
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:45,800
Let's go.

469
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,360
FELLI: Oh no.

470
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:52,440
LAYFON: The monument's
been overrun.

471
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,720
NINA: This is‐‐

472
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:54,520
What's the matter?

473
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,920
FELLI: Do you know
this place, Nina?

474
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:01,760
NINA: Yes.

475
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:03,120
It's Gandoweria.

476
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,760
The city we fought
two years ago.

477
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:05,560
SHARNID: Yeah.

478
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:06,560
You're right.

479
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:10,120
And they defeated us in that
battle too, didn't they?

480
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:11,880
So what the hell happened here?

481
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:15,480
And just how long has it been
since the city was attacked?

482
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:16,400
SHARNID: Who knows?

483
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:19,040
Maybe they got hit right
after they beat Zuellni.

484
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,480
No.

485
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:22,040
No, this is impossible.

486
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:24,200
After beating Zuellni,
Gandoweria had plenty

487
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,840
of mines to power itself with.

488
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:28,000
And the city's fighting
strength and coordination

489
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:28,840
were second to none.

490
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:31,560
LAYFON: That means nothing.

491
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:32,800
I told you.

492
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:35,920
You can't be right.

493
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:39,560
You can win a battle or a
mine, but it doesn't matter.

494
00:20:39,560 --> 00:20:42,920
Not to the Contaminoids.

495
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:45,440
Nina.

496
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:48,440
[MUSIC PLAYING]

497
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:23,240
It's all meaningless.

498
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,560
Can I ask you a question?

499
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:30,560
LAYFON: Of course.

500
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:35,040
What is it that you
would consider a victory?

501
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:38,280
For me, it's just
about surviving.

502
00:21:38,280 --> 00:21:41,720
Both for myself and all
those I want to protect, too.

503
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:45,160
Victory is when none of us die.

504
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:48,160
[SHATTERING]

505
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:49,640
Hey.

506
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:50,640
Look out!

507
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:57,160
[CRASHING]

508
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:07,360
GORNEO: Just surviving is a
disgrace for a military artist,

509
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:10,200
but you know all about that.

510
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,000
After all, you are
the one who forever

511
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,760
sullied the name of
the Heaven's Blades

512
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:16,440
and was expelled for your crime.

513
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:19,400
Is that true?

514
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:22,400
[MUSIC PLAYING]

515
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,480
MAN (VOICEOVER): In the
midst of their expedition,

516
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:04,240
Gorneo tells Nina of
Layfon's past crime.

517
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:06,920
Meanwhile, in Glendan, the
mystery behind Leerin's stalker

518
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:07,840
grows deeper.

519
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:11,120
And Savaris and Lintens must
stop them before it's too late.

520
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:15,720
Next time, the Right to be a
Heaven's Blade and Restoration.

